    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 10.0,
      "narration_text": "Draw both curves on the same time axis. Fluent conditions produce a spike that decays. Frictional conditions produce a smaller initial peak that persists.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "drawon"
      },
      "scene_class": "B07_DrawCurves",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.51,
      "audio_file": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-two-clocks/clips/B07.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B07.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "As time passes, the fluent curve falls below the frictional one. The student who felt confused is now ahead. The curves cross, and they stay crossed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "transform"
      },
      "scene_class": "B08_CrossPoint",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.51,
      "audio_file": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-two-clocks/clips/B08.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B08.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "The student who feels they are mastering the material under fluent conditions is often learning less than the student who feels confused under more friction. The fluency is the trap.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "DOCUMENT",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "highlight"
      },
      "scene_class": "B09_QuoteStruggle",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.8,
      "audio_file": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-two-clocks/clips/B09.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B09.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 8.0,
      "narration_text": "The difference is storage strength \u2014 how deeply the material is encoded. Fluent conditions produce high performance with low storage strength. Frictional conditions produce lower performance with high storage strength.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "scene_class": "B10_StorageStrength",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.89,
      "audio_file": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-two-clocks/clips/B10.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B10.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "THE IMPLICATION",
      "estimated_duration_s": 7.0,
      "narration_text": "Borrowed certainty has no storage strength to retrieve. Performance decays monotonically and the spacing effect is absent.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "DOCUMENT",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "highlight"
      },
      "scene_class": "B11_QuoteDecay",
      "actual_duration_s": 7.0,
      "audio_file": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-two-clocks/clips/B11.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B11.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "act": "THE EXAMPLE",
      "estimated_duration_s": 12.0,
      "narration_text": "A company redesigns new-hire onboarding. One cohort watches polished explainer videos \u2014 they rate the experience eight out of ten. Two weeks later, retention tests average 41 percent. A second cohort uses retrieval practice instead \u2014 harder, they rate it six out of ten. Two weeks later, retention: 73 percent. The cohort that found it harder remembered more. The fluency was measuring the video, not the learning.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "scene_class": "B12_ExampleTwoClocks",
      "audio_file": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 27.66,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-two-clocks/clips/B12.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-two-clocks/mp3/beat-B12.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B13",
      "act": "RECAP",
      "estimated_duration_s": 9.0,
      "narration_text": "Fluency signals performance, not learning. The struggle is the trace of learning happening.",
